Title : Portal:Current events/2014 May 3
Text : <!-- All news items below this line -->{{Current events header|2014|05|03}}

;Armed conflicts and attacks
*[[Law enforcement in India|Indian police]] arrest 29 people after [[National Democratic Front of Bodoland]] separatists kill 29 Muslims and burn down homes. [http://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/indian-army-called-rebels-kill-29-muslims-23574827 (AP via ABC News America)]
*The [[Armed Forces of Ukraine]] resume an offensive near [[Kramatorsk]], as military observers from the [[Organization for Security and Cooperation in Europe]] are released after having been held hostage for a week. [http://www.foxnews.com/world/2014/05/03/ukraine-unrest-spreads/ (Fox News)]
*Twin explosions are reported in the city of [[Mombasa]], [[Kenya]], with at least three people killed and several injured. [https://www.bbc.com/news/world-africa-27272072 (BBC)]

;Art and culture
*The [[61st National Film Awards]] are presented by the [[President of India]] to honour the best films of 2013 in  [[Indian cinema]].
**[[Gulzar]] receives [[Dadasaheb Phalke Award]] while ''[[Ship of Theseus (film)|Ship of Theseus]]'' wins the [[National Film Award for Best Feature Film|Best Feature Film award]]. [https://variety.com/2014/film/news/ship-of-theseus-wins-indias-national-film-award-1201158125/ (Variety)]

;Disasters and accidents
*The death toll from [[2014 Badakhshan mudslides|the mudslides]] in [[Afghanistan]] rises to 2,100, with 4,000 people displaced. [http://www.abc.net.au/news/2014-05-03/afghanistan-landslide-villages-hundreds-feared-dead/5428048 (ABC)]

;Health and environment
*The first U.S. case of [[Middle East respiratory syndrome|MERS]] is reported in [[Munster, Indiana]], of someone who travelled to [[Saudi Arabia]]. [http://www.cnn.com/2014/05/02/health/indiana-mers/ (CNN)]

;Law and crime
*A gunman shoots and kills 3 people and wounds 4 others in [[Jonesboro, Arkansas]], U.S., and then dies. [http://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/gunman-killed-arkansas-shootings-23579410 (ABC News)]
*[[Murder of Jean McConville]] and [[Arrest of Gerry Adams]]:
**A mural of [[Sinn Fein]] Leader [[Gerry Adams]] is painted on a wall on the [[Falls Road, Belfast|Falls Road]], [[Belfast]], as police are granted a further 48 hours to question him about the murder of [[Jean McConville]]. [https://www.bbc.com/news/uk-northern-ireland-27272797 (BBC)]

;Sport
*In American [[horse racing]], [[California Chrome]] ridden by [[Victor Espinoza]] wins the [[2014 Kentucky Derby]]. [http://fansided.com/2014/05/03/california-chrome-wins-2014-kentucky-derby-twitter-reacts/#!HTUbw (Sports Illustrated Fan Sided)]
;Television
*[[Hub Network]] Episodes of [[My Little Pony: Friendship Is Magic]], [[Transformers: Rescue Bots]], [[Spooksville (TV series)|Spooksville]] and [[Sabrina: Secrets of a Teenage Witch]]
*Sequels to the Episodes: [[Sabrina the Teenage Witch (1970 TV series)|Sabrina the Teenage Witch]] (1970-1974), [[Sabrina the Teenage Witch (1996 TV series)|Sabrina the Teenage Witch]] (1997-2003), [[Sabrina: The Animated Series]] (1999-2000) and [[Sabrina's Secret Life]] (2004)
